Here's the full **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit of your `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests`:

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| High | 3 | 3 |
| Medium | 1 | 1 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **4** |

---

## Findings by Severity

### 🔴 HIGH — Sleepy Test

**Smell:** Sleepy Test (testsmells.org #3)
**Test:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 82)
**Integration calibration:** Even for integration tests, `Thread.Sleep` is a smell because it introduces non-determinism and inflates suite duration.

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000); // ← blocks thread for 3 seconds unconditionally
```

**Fix:** Replace with a polling/retry pattern or async event:
```csharp
var timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(3);
var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
while (sw.Elapsed < timeout)
{
    if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id)) break;
    await Task.Delay(50);
}
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id));
```

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Conditional Test Logic

**Smell:** Conditional Test Logic (testsmells.org #1)
**Test:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (line 94)
**Rationale:** The `if/else` means one branch is always dead — you're never testing both paths in a single run.

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Fix:** Split into two deterministic tests with explicit setup:
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_WhenStandard_ReturnsName() { /* insert standard, assert name */ }

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_WhenPremium_HasDiscount() { /* insert premium, assert rate */ }
```

---

### 🔴 HIGH — Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Smell:** Unknown Test / Empty Test (testsmells.org #4)
**Test:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (line 113)
**Rationale:** This test passes even if every insert silently fails. It provides false confidence.

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User(...));
    // ← No assertion
}
```

**Fix:** Assert the observable outcome:
```csharp
for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
    _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));

Assert.AreEqual(100, _repository.ListAll().Count);
```

---

### 🟡 MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette

**Smell:** Assertion Roulette (extended catalog)
**Test:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (line 28)
**Rationale:** 4 assertions with no message parameters — a failure on CI reports only a line number.

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

**Fix:** Add messages or (preferred in MSTest 4.x) use the fluent `Assert.That` overloads:
```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Auto-generated Id should be positive");
```

---

## Smells Scanned — No Findings

| Smell | Status |
|-------|--------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean — in-memory SQLite is a proper test fake |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean — methods test a single operation per test (integration calibration applied) |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean — `3` in `ListUsers` is contextually obvious (3 inserts → count 3) |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Not present |
| Exception Handling | ✅ No try/catch in tests |
| General Fixture | ✅ Both fields used by all tests |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ None skipped |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Uses `[TestInitialize]` correctly |
| Default Test | ✅ Properly named |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Not present |
| Redundant Print/Assertion | ✅ Not present |

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Effort |
|----------|-------|-----|--------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add one assert | ~1 min |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into 2 tests | ~5 min |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | Replace with poll loop | ~10 min |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | Add message strings | ~3 min |

**Bottom line:** 4 of 8 tests are clean and well-structured. The 3 high-severity findings represent real risk (false passes, dead paths, flakiness). The Assertion Roulette is cosmetic but helps CI debuggability. Overall the suite's architecture (in-memory DB, proper setup/teardown) is solid — the issues are localized and quick to fix.
